\begin_layout Standard
\noindent
Lucas Benedičič was born on December 12, 1977 in Buenos Aires, Argentina.
 He was a student at the University of Buenos Aires, where he completed
 the first 4 years of the undergraduate programme in computer sciences,
 at the Faculty of Exact and Natural Sciences.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
After moving to Slovenia in 2002, he enrolled into the University of Ljubljana,
 Faculty of Computer and Information Science, where he graduated in 2007
 with the work titled 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Application development using open-source technologies
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In September 2007, he started his postgraduate studies at the University
 of Primorska, Faculty of Mathematics, Natural Sciences and Information
 Technologies, after enrolling into the Masters study programme of computer
 sciences.
 He graduated in 2009 with the work titled 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Optimization of Common Pilot Channels in UMTS Networks
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Towards the end of 2007, he was awarded a scholarship for continuing his
 postgraduate studies in Slovenia.
 The award was received after winning a problem-solving contest, organized
 by Halcom, d.d.
 In the fall of 2009, he enrolled in the PhD program entitled 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Information and Communication Technologies
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

